        {
            "_id": "srziEIkqbGijOabG",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Repel Boarders!",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The naval crew chooses a single direction and smashes into its enemies to push them in that direction. The troop attempts one Athletics check to [[/act shove]] and compares the result to the Fortitude DC of all enemies that are adjacent to the troop and in the chosen direction. The direction can be straight or diagonal, and the GM determines which enemies can be affected. If at least one enemy was moved, the troop can Stride to follow as described in Shove; the troop can move any number of its segments when it does, and this Stride doesn't trigger reactions.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
